 rode out of the villiage in the direction she sensed from her feathered friend. She rode in silence, hard and fast to where she was needed. She was barely tired when she entered the forest. Her owl was now flying from place to place, showing his master the way until he stopped. Solari quietly made her way towards the group digging the holes. <br>
