<br>
 &quot;You are weak amazon. Just like the others of your kind I killed in the arena.&quot; he said mockingly as she wiped blood from his face. <br>
<br>
Solari reached for her dagger, not finding it attached to her belt, she looked around quickly for it. Laying several feet away on the ground where she had first landed, lay her dagger. Solari moved quickly to retrieve it, but was stabbed in the leg by the soldier. Wincing, she grabbed the soldier's hand and began to squeeze it, crushing the bones. She punched him in the face as she continued her death grip on his crushed hand, forcing him towards where her dagger lay. She laid another punch to his face, sending him flying to the ground, then she slowly leaned over to get her dagger. <br>
<br>
 &quot;If you still think that I am weak, Roman, then come and get me.&quot; She offered as her instinct of wild rage began to take control, dancing her dagger between each hand. <br>
